background.js - according the chrome extensions API, this file contains listeners and define the functions that will be called when clicking the menu and the extension's icon.
It also contain a respond listener that receive the selected word and it's context. The listener calls the dictionary for definition , add the word to the local storage and call the code in show_contexts_jquery.js

getSel.js - a code that gets the selected word and it's context from the page and send a request that the background is listening to.

manage.js - the code in this file deals with the management of words and contexts (executed when the user clicks on the extension icon) 

show_contexts_jquery.js - create the popup of the word definition and the list of it's contexts
